   - `∫_{a}^{b} sin(x / 2 + 3) dx = F(b) - F(a) = -2 * cos(b / 2 + 3) - (-2 * cos(a / 2 + 3))`.

3. Simplify the result to get `2 * cos(a / 2 + 3) - 2 * cos(b / 2 + 3)`.

